title: Secret Origins
description:
Secret Origins was a 50-issue series (plus three annuals and a special) that ran from 1986 to 1990, published by DC Comics. Typically, an issue would be given over to clarifying the post-Crisis origins of a number of characters, usually two (as most of the issues were 'double-sized', i.e. 48 pages, plus ads). Roy Thomas was the initial writer/editorial consultant on the series; later issues were overseen by Mark Waid.

Also included is the original Secret Origins series from the early 70s, as well as several one-shots from 1960s and 1970s, 1990s.


Released on http://ComicPirates.info
